@node Req "Information about the REQ.LIBRARY"
The REQ.LIBRARY was written by Bruce Dawson and Colin Fox.  For space
considerations, only the main executable has been included.  If you need
to use this library (1.x users) if you can't find the complete REQ.LIBRARY
archive (including documentation) please contact Legendary and we will
provide it free of charge.
@endnode

@node SMPlay "SMPlay CLI Program"
SMPlay is a CLI/Shell only program that allows you to play sound files
directly, using the keyboard.

It can be very useful for scripts (like having a sound play in your
startup-sequence), or for launching from directory-oriented programs like
DirMaster or Directory Opus.

It is also useful for your C directory as it takes up less memory and
is good for those who like the keyboard more than the mouse.
@endnode
